you do nothing you don't wanna do.

714
01:04:11,086 --> 01:04:14,621
We'll just go back
to what we was doing, that's all.

715
01:04:18,218 --> 01:04:20,294
- I want it.
- What?

716
01:04:20,345 --> 01:04:22,421
I said I want it!

717
01:04:22,472 --> 01:04:27,348
- Baby, I can't hear you!
- I wanna be a singer, Doo!

718
01:04:27,394 --> 01:04:29,470
I want it real bad.

719
01:04:31,440 --> 01:04:33,598
I want it real bad.

720
01:04:35,319 --> 01:04:37,857
Jack, you see that row of numbers?

721
01:04:37,905 --> 01:04:42,068
That tells you how many miles
you've gone, how far we've been.

722
01:04:42,117 --> 01:04:44,952
I love you
and I'll see you when we come home.

723
01:04:44,995 --> 01:04:46,869
Come on, girl.

724
01:04:46,914 --> 01:04:48,990
- Mommy, I love you.
- I love you.

725
01:04:50,250 --> 01:04:52,920
Betty Sue, you take care
of the little ones.

726
01:04:52,961 --> 01:04:55,333
Will you mind Grandma? OK?

727
01:04:55,380 --> 01:04:58,417
Bye, Jack! Bye, Ernest Ray! Bye-bye.

728
01:05:01,386 --> 01:05:05,882
I left y'all some Tootsie Rolls
in the top drawer in the bedroom!

729
01:05:05,933 --> 01:05:07,890
- Bye-bye!
- Bye, Mommy!

730
01:05:07,935 --> 01:05:11,469
- Bye, Mommy!
- Come back, Mommy!

731
01:05:11,521 --> 01:05:13,597
(Changing radio stations)

732
01:05:16,902 --> 01:05:21,279
(DJ) <i>Now here's that number one hit,
Walkin' After Midnight.</i>

733
01:05:21,323 --> 01:05:24,906
- Patsy Cline.
- That's right, that's WCBL.

734
01:05:24,952 --> 01:05:27,028
Disc jockey name of Bobby Day.

735
01:05:27,079 --> 01:05:29,700
Keep your eyes open for the transmitter.

736
01:05:29,748 --> 01:05:32,619
- The what?
- The transmitter.

737
01:05:32,668 --> 01:05:37,211
<i>♪ ...always walkin' after midnight ♪</i>

738
01:05:37,255 --> 01:05:41,834
<i>♪ Searching for you ♪</i>

739
01:05:43,011 --> 01:05:48,088
<i>♪ I walked for miles along the highway ♪</i>

740
01:05:48,141 --> 01:05:51,308
<i>♪ Well, that's just my way... ♪♪</i>

741
01:05:51,853 --> 01:05:53,645
(Radio, car engine off)

742
01:05:56,858 --> 01:06:00,773
Dadgummit, Doo, wait a minute!
People can see in here.

743
01:06:00,821 --> 01:06:03,987
- Hurry up, let's go.
- What do I say?

744
01:06:04,032 --> 01:06:07,816
Don't even think about it, darlin',
just start talking.

745
01:06:13,041 --> 01:06:15,746
...to see a weeping willow...
- (Knocking)

746
01:06:15,794 --> 01:06:18,546
Crying on his pillow

747
01:06:18,588 --> 01:06:23,416
Maybe he's crying for me

748
01:06:23,468 --> 01:06:26,173
And as the skies turn gloomy...

749
01:06:26,221 --> 01:06:28,926
I'm sorry, folks, no visitors allowed.

750
01:06:29,975 --> 01:06:32,548
Hi, Bobby. My name's Loretta Lynn

751
01:06:32,602 --> 01:06:37,514
and I sent you a picture
and my newest record on the Zero label.

752
01:06:37,566 --> 01:06:39,938
No kidding, you can't be in here.

753
01:06:41,319 --> 01:06:44,523
It's a song I wrote
called Honky Tonk Girl.

754
01:06:44,573 --> 01:06:47,858
- I got the idea...
- I got it and I played it

755
01:06:47,909 --> 01:06:50,697
and it just sorta laid right there.

756
01:06:50,746 --> 01:06:53,746
So thanks for coming in, you all.
Bye-bye, now.

757
01:06:54,833 --> 01:06:56,660
Bye-bye.

758
01:06:56,710 --> 01:07:00,494
You're listening to Tri-State Country
with Bobby Day

759
01:07:00,547 --> 01:07:02,705
right here till six o'clock.

760
01:07:02,758 --> 01:07:07,218
Here's a word from our friends
down at Hutchins' Hot Pigs. (Snorts)

761
01:07:07,262 --> 01:07:09,800
Tell them all about it, Hutch.

762
01:07:09,848 --> 01:07:13,715
You played it? You ain't even took it
out of the wrapper.

763
01:07:13,769 --> 01:07:19,522
You know how many records I get?
I don't have time to play all of them.

764
01:07:19,566 --> 01:07:21,642
Why did you lie to us?

765
01:07:21,693 --> 01:07:25,738
Why'd you say they didn't like us?
Doo worked so hard!

766
01:07:25,781 --> 01:07:28,698
- (Ranting)
- Get her out. I gotta go on the air.

767
01:07:28,742 --> 01:07:32,526
I'm sorry but there's nothing I can do
when she gets like this.

768
01:07:32,579 --> 01:07:34,868
He took the picture too.

769
01:07:34,915 --> 01:07:37,916
Heck, we got four babies
we had to leave home.

770
01:07:37,959 --> 01:07:41,874
We drove all the way here,
spent every last dime we had.

771
01:07:41,922 --> 01:07:46,714
- We got a treat for you here today...
- Now you're saying nobody likes it...

772
01:07:46,760 --> 01:07:51,718
I can't believe it! I can't believe
you'd do something so mean as that!

773
01:07:51,765 --> 01:07:54,635
- Tell them all about yourself.
- About myself?

774
01:08:01,733 --> 01:08:04,271
(Radio) <i>Then I sung it for Doolittle.</i>

775
01:08:04,319 --> 01:08:08,566
Everybody calls him Mooney because
he sold moonshine in Butcher Hollow.

776
01:08:08,615 --> 01:08:10,524
- Where?
- <i>Butcher Hollow,</i>

777
01:08:10,575 --> 01:08:12,947
<i>where we're from back in Kentucky.</i>

778
01:08:12,994 --> 01:08:14,254
<i>Anyway,</i>

779
01:08:14,304 --> 01:08:18,488
I wrote the song and Doo said,
"That's the prettiest song I ever heard,

780
01:08:18,542 --> 01:08:20,415
"good as Patsy Cline."

781
01:08:20,460 --> 01:08:22,998
I said, "Nobody sings as good as Patsy."

782
01:08:23,046 --> 01:08:26,581
<i>Let's listen to it, folks,
brand-new on the Zero label,</i>

783
01:08:26,633 --> 01:08:29,206
- <i>Miss Lorene Lynn singing...</i>
- What?

784
01:08:29,261 --> 01:08:31,337
Honky Tonk Girl.

785
01:08:31,388 --> 01:08:34,009
It's Loretta Lynn, not Lorene.

786
01:08:34,057 --> 01:08:35,884
- Loretta?
- Uh-huh.

787
01:08:35,934 --> 01:08:39,054
(Radio: Honky Tonk Girl)

788
01:08:43,066 --> 01:08:46,186
Girl, you sure got over
being bashful fast.

789
01:08:46,236 --> 01:08:50,186
I done what you said -
just opened my mouth and out it come.

790
01:08:50,240 --> 01:08:54,617
I didn't have no more notion of
what I was gonna say than a rabbit.

791
01:08:54,661 --> 01:08:56,950
You keep on being a rabbit.

792
01:08:56,997 --> 01:09:00,366
You want me to watch for
the next transmitter?

793
01:09:00,417 --> 01:09:03,868
Hell, yes, watch out for that transmitter.
(Laughing)

794
01:09:03,920 --> 01:09:08,629
<i>♪ We were so happy,
my heart was in a whirl... ♪♪</i>

795
01:09:08,675 --> 01:09:12,839
(DJ) <i>WTNT, the voice of country
in Hazard, Kentucky.</i>

796
01:09:12,888 --> 01:09:17,265
(Loretta) <i>We've seen all different places
and met all kinds of people</i>

797
01:09:17,309 --> 01:09:19,385
<i>and Doolittle, he's driving...</i>

798
01:09:19,436 --> 01:09:21,393
(DJ) <i>WMIT in Middlesboro...</i>

799
01:09:21,438 --> 01:09:25,898
(Loretta) <i>Momma's back in Kentucky
taking care of the four babies.</i>

800
01:09:25,942 --> 01:09:28,018
(DJ) <i>Top Ridge, Tennessee...</i>

801
01:09:28,069 --> 01:09:31,189
(Loretta) <i>I had no idea
where singers got songs</i>

802
01:09:31,239 --> 01:09:36,909
<i>so I thought I'd better write myself one
till I get this music business figured out.</i>

803
01:09:39,998 --> 01:09:48,124
(Radio) <i>♪ Compared to the man
with a satisfied mind ♪</i>

804
01:09:48,173 --> 01:09:50,878
Doo, can we send
the kids some suckers?

805
01:09:50,926 --> 01:09:53,417
No, baby, we can't afford it.

806
01:09:53,470 --> 01:09:55,759
There's your baloney, 48 cents.

807
01:09:55,805 --> 01:09:57,964
I'm getting so sick of baloney.

808
01:09:58,016 --> 01:10:02,559
- You know what they say about it?
- What?

809
01:10:02,604 --> 01:10:04,478
Makes you horny.

810
01:10:04,522 --> 01:10:06,599
What's that mean?

811
01:10:06,983 --> 01:10:10,352
Are you so dadburned ignorant
you don't know?

812
01:10:10,403 --> 01:10:13,689
- No. What does it mean?
- Ain't gonna tell you.

813
01:10:13,740 --> 01:10:15,614
Doo!

814
01:10:16,952 --> 01:10:19,324
Doo, what does it mean?

815
01:10:20,747 --> 01:10:24,745
(DJ) <i>All these months on the road
have you hit Nashville yet?</i>

816
01:10:24,793 --> 01:10:29,502
<i>No, sir, but I'm dying to.</i>
I'm gonna get on the Grand Ole Opry too.

817
01:10:29,547 --> 01:10:33,592
Sometimes you gotta pay a lot of dues
to get on the Opry.

818
01:10:33,635 --> 01:10:38,344
- Pay dues?
- It takes years and years of hard work.

819
01:10:38,390 --> 01:10:43,135
(DJ) <i>Still, from the looks of things,
you're off to a real good start.</i>

820
01:10:43,186 --> 01:10:47,018
We've been driving so much
I don't know where I am half the time.

821
01:10:47,065 --> 01:10:51,229
Oh, it's fun, though, you know,
we... we sing and talk

822
01:10:51,278 --> 01:10:53,235
and Doo, that's my husband,

823
01:10:53,280 --> 01:10:55,521
- he'll get to acting horny.
- What?

824
01:10:55,573 --> 01:10:59,073
- <i>The more I laugh the hornier he gets.</i>
- Goddamn!

825
01:10:59,119 --> 01:11:02,488
He'll say, "Spread me up
a baloney sandwich!"

826
01:11:02,539 --> 01:11:05,326
I don't know where
you think you are, lady,

827
01:11:05,375 --> 01:11:08,376
but that kind of smut
don't go on in these parts.

828
01:11:08,420 --> 01:11:12,631
I didn't know it was dirty.
I thought horny meant acting silly.

829
01:11:12,674 --> 01:11:14,999
Come off that dumb hillbilly act.

830
01:11:15,051 --> 01:11:18,052
- Mister, that ain't no act.
- Thank you, Doo.

831
01:11:18,096 --> 01:11:19,756
Let me tell you something.

832
01:11:19,806 --> 01:11:23,175
We're gonna be damn lucky
not to lose our FCC licence.

833
01:11:23,226 --> 01:11:26,560
- And I mean damn lucky!
- (Phones ringing)

834
01:11:26,604 --> 01:11:30,934
I ain't never playing another
record of yours on this radio station!

835
01:11:30,984 --> 01:11:34,435
Don't you ever think
what the hell you're saying?

836
01:11:34,487 --> 01:11:36,610
- You told me not to!
- Wait!

837
01:11:36,656 --> 01:11:41,365
Wait up. Don't worry about him.
If you're on the charts you'll get played.

838
01:11:41,411 --> 01:11:43,487
What charts?

839
01:11:43,538 --> 01:11:47,073
You got a hit record.
You don't know that?

840
01:11:47,125 --> 01:11:49,830
That really isn't an act, is it?

841
01:11:49,878 --> 01:11:52,832
Look here - Cash Box magazine,
came out today.

842
01:11:52,881 --> 01:11:55,668
You're number 14 nationwide.

843
01:11:55,717 --> 01:11:58,208
You really didn't know.

844
01:12:03,558 --> 01:12:05,100
Thank you.
Doo...

845
01:12:05,143 --> 01:12:07,848
(Radio: Patsy Cline - Crazy)

846
01:12:10,148 --> 01:12:13,268
- (DJ) <i>And now...</i>
- I love you, Doo.

847
01:12:13,318 --> 01:12:16,070
<i>...for the girl with roses on her pillow,</i>

848
01:12:16,112 --> 01:12:19,279
<i>here's Patsy Cline's
number one hit, Crazy.</i>

849
01:12:19,324 --> 01:12:21,945
<i>♪ Crazy ♪</i>

850
01:12:21,993 --> 01:12:31,994
<i>♪ I'm crazy for feeling so lonely ♪</i>

851
01:12:32,045 --> 01:12:35,663
<i>♪ I'm crazy ♪</i>

852
01:12:35,715 --> 01:12:45,052
<i>♪ Crazy for feeling so blue ♪</i>

853
01:12:46,142 --> 01:12:48,894
<i>♪ I knew ♪</i>

854
01:12:48,937 --> 01:12:52,519
<i>♪ You'd love me as long... ♪♪</i>

855
01:12:56,027 --> 01:12:58,150
Doolittle?

856
01:13:01,825 --> 01:13:04,826
Doo? Doo?

857
01:13:21,261 --> 01:13:23,134
(Car horn)

858
01:13:26,933 --> 01:13:30,219
That old building
sure would hold a lot of hay!

859
01:13:30,270 --> 01:13:32,346
This is the Grand Ole Opry.

860
01:13:32,397 --> 01:13:36,395
- You want chocolate or glazed?
- The Grand Ole Opry!

861
01:13:36,443 --> 01:13:38,316
What if they won't let me in?

862
01:13:38,361 --> 01:13:42,193
They'd better, I spent all the money
on these doughnuts.

863
01:13:42,240 --> 01:13:44,316
How are they gonna keep us out?

864
01:13:46,494 --> 01:13:48,902
We're number 14!

865
01:13:48,955 --> 01:13:50,782
Nationwide.

866
01:13:54,878 --> 01:13:58,377
♪ I'm walkin' the floor over you ♪

867
01:13:59,466 --> 01:14:03,297
♪ I can't sleep a wink, that is true ♪

868
01:14:04,387 --> 01:14:09,049
♪ I'm hoping and I'm praying
as my heart breaks right in two ♪

869
01:14:09,100 --> 01:14:12,635
♪ Walkin' the floor over you ♪

870
01:14:13,730 --> 01:14:18,273
♪ You left me and you went away ♪

871
01:14:18,318 --> 01:14:22,861
♪ You said that
you'd be back in just a day ♪

872
01:14:22,906 --> 01:14:27,698
- ♪ You've broken your promise... ♪
- Are you Loretta Lynn? Loretta Lynn?

873
01:14:27,744 --> 01:14:31,243
Loretta Lynn? Loretta Lynn?

874
01:14:31,289 --> 01:14:35,038
You Loretta Lynn?
I've been calling and calling you.

875
01:14:35,084 --> 01:14:37,658
Mr. Devine says to put you
on Ernest's show.

876
01:14:37,712 --> 01:14:41,128
Stand over yonder.
Keep your eyes on Ernest.

877
01:14:41,174 --> 01:14:45,124
He'll introduce you
if the show ain't running too long.

878
01:14:45,178 --> 01:14:47,633
♪ ...As my heart breaks right in two ♪

879
01:14:47,680 --> 01:14:49,590
♪ Walkin' the floor over you... ♪

880
01:14:49,641 --> 01:14:51,135
What's the matter with you?

881
01:14:51,184 --> 01:14:53,260
- I'm scared.
- Scared? Goddamn!

882
01:14:53,311 --> 01:14:54,936
I don't belong here.

883
01:14:54,979 --> 01:14:58,265
You belong as much as anybody. Relax.

884
01:14:58,316 --> 01:15:01,650
I ain't ready.
I ain't paid my dues to be here.

885
01:15:01,694 --> 01:15:03,770
We'll pay 'em later on.

886
01:15:03,821 --> 01:15:08,115
♪ Someday you may be lonesome too... ♪

887
01:15:08,159 --> 01:15:10,033
Where you going?

888
01:15:10,078 --> 01:15:12,651
I can't stand a nervous woman.

889
01:15:12,705 --> 01:15:14,365
Don't leave.

890
01:15:14,415 --> 01:15:18,034
I ain't leaving,
I'm just going to get some fresh air!

891
01:15:18,086 --> 01:15:21,289
♪ I love you and I will the day I die ♪

892
01:15:22,215 --> 01:15:25,714
♪ I'm walkin' the floor over you ♪

893
01:15:26,803 --> 01:15:30,753
♪ I can't sleep a wink, that is true... ♪♪

894
01:15:31,849 --> 01:15:34,340
(Men arguing)

895
01:15:38,481 --> 01:15:41,399
Ain't got no place in here for drunks.

896
01:15:41,442 --> 01:15:43,850
We don't want no trouble. Go home.

897
01:15:43,903 --> 01:15:46,311
- (Applause)
- Thank you all.

898
01:15:46,364 --> 01:15:51,156
Thank you and welcome
to this portion of our Grand Ole Opry.

899
01:15:51,202 --> 01:15:56,030
I want you to meet a little gal
that I'm sure you're going to love.

900
01:15:56,082 --> 01:15:59,000
Let's give a big Grand Ole Opry welcome

901
01:15:59,043 --> 01:16:01,581
to Miss Loretta Lynn!

902
01:16:10,513 --> 01:16:12,506
Get out there.

903
01:16:12,557 --> 01:16:15,012
If you ain't a picker, what are you?

904
01:16:15,059 --> 01:16:19,935
- Got a wife singing on the Opry.
- I see. One of the husbands.

905
01:16:19,981 --> 01:16:23,397
Well, I'm one of the wives, darling.

906
01:16:23,443 --> 01:16:26,776
- See you later.
- Hey, hey. How about a drink?

907
01:16:26,821 --> 01:16:29,656
She's on right now, she's on the radio!

908
01:16:29,699 --> 01:16:32,486
Hey, buddy, could you turn the radio up?

909
01:16:32,535 --> 01:16:35,619
♪ ...nothing but wrong ♪

910
01:16:35,663 --> 01:16:40,824
♪ Many nights I've laid awake and cried ♪

911
01:16:42,670 --> 01:16:45,707
♪ We were so happy ♪

912
01:16:45,757 --> 01:16:49,173
♪ My heart was in a whirl ♪

913
01:16:49,218 --> 01:16:54,639
♪ But now I'm a honky tonk girl ♪

914
01:16:57,602 --> 01:16:59,974
(Man) Hey, sweet thing!

915
01:17:00,021 --> 01:17:02,097
Sweet thing!

916
01:17:04,192 --> 01:17:06,315
How's that husband of yours?

917
01:17:06,361 --> 01:17:08,852
Trying to sober up to do his show.

918
01:17:08,905 --> 01:17:10,981
Turn the radio up, will you?

919
01:17:11,032 --> 01:17:14,199
Listen, I'm trying to hear the radio.
Turn it up!

920
01:17:14,243 --> 01:17:16,569
He's got a wife on the Opry.

921
01:17:16,621 --> 01:17:20,571
Oh, is that right?
Hell, you got it made, man!

922
01:17:20,625 --> 01:17:24,041
All you gotta do is count it
as the old lady rakes it in.

923
01:17:24,087 --> 01:17:26,163
I do my share. Turn it up!

924
01:17:26,214 --> 01:17:28,290
Sure you do, Hoss, sure you do.

925
01:17:28,341 --> 01:17:31,674
I'm trying to hear my wife sing
on the radio.

926
01:17:31,719 --> 01:17:35,468
Is that your job?
She sings and you listen? (Laughs)

927
01:17:39,227 --> 01:17:45,597
♪ And now I'm a honky tonk girl ♪♪

928
01:17:50,196 --> 01:17:52,402
I'll be!

929
01:17:53,491 --> 01:17:55,697
Wonderful.

930
01:17:55,743 --> 01:17:58,234
Real wonderful, honey, thank you.

931
01:17:58,287 --> 01:18:02,202
By the way, you think you might
come back next week?

932
01:18:03,000 --> 01:18:08,042
- I ain't got nothing else planned.
- She ain't got... OK, Loretta Lynn!

933
01:18:10,258 --> 01:18:12,334
(Ernest) She's a doll, I'll tell you.

934
01:18:12,385 --> 01:18:14,045
Thank you, honey.

935
01:18:15,221 --> 01:18:17,759
Doo, did you hear? They loved me!

936
01:18:17,807 --> 01:18:20,974
They want me back next week,
can you believe it?

937
01:18:21,018 --> 01:18:25,727
I can. Now we gotta sit down
and plan what we're gonna do next.

938
01:18:25,773 --> 01:18:28,644
I'm too happy to think about that now.

939
01:18:28,693 --> 01:18:30,769
I don't care if I die tomorrow,

940
01:18:30,820 --> 01:18:35,233
if I never sing another song,
it ain't never gonna be better than this.

941
01:18:35,283 --> 01:18:38,034
Did you hurt yourself?
Your jaw's swollen.

942
01:18:38,077 --> 01:18:41,992
That's just from grinning,
that's from pure happiness.

943
01:18:42,039 --> 01:18:49,122
(Loretta) ♪ I fall to pieces ♪

944
01:18:50,590 --> 01:18:55,715
♪ How can I be just your friend? ♪

945
01:18:57,221 --> 01:19:03,473
♪ You want me to act
like we've never kissed ♪

946
01:19:04,604 --> 01:19:07,640
♪ You want me to forget ♪

947
01:19:08,733 --> 01:19:12,184
♪ Pretend we've never met ♪

948
01:19:13,780 --> 01:19:17,694
♪ And I've tried and I've tried ♪

949
01:19:17,742 --> 01:19:20,447
♪ But I haven't yet ♪

950
01:19:21,537 --> 01:19:28,703
♪ You walk by and I fall to pieces... ♪

951
01:19:28,753 --> 01:19:32,453
Friends, this is a number one hit song
by Miss Patsy Cline.

952
01:19:32,548 --> 01:19:36,712
Y'all all know she's in the hospital
cos she's been in a car wreck.

953
01:19:36,761 --> 01:19:39,133
I wanna dedicate this song to her.

954
01:19:39,180 --> 01:19:42,715
Patsy, if you're listening,
this song is for you.

955
01:19:46,771 --> 01:19:54,067
♪ I fall to pieces... ♪

956
01:19:58,866 --> 01:20:01,571
Oh, thank you.

957
01:20:02,870 --> 01:20:05,242
Loretta, Patsy Cline's husband.

958
01:20:05,289 --> 01:20:07,282
- Charlie Dick.
- Hello.

959
01:20:07,333 --> 01:20:11,912
Patsy heard you, she wants you
to come and see her. Can you come?

960
01:20:11,963 --> 01:20:14,880
This is Charlie Dick,
Patsy Cline's husband.

961
01:20:14,924 --> 01:20:18,340
She was listening.
She wants to meet me. Can we go?

962
01:20:18,386 --> 01:20:22,549
Sure, go ahead. I'll take the young'uns.
Get your momma's guitar.

963
01:20:22,598 --> 01:20:24,757
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

964
01:20:24,809 --> 01:20:27,976
OK, honey,
Momma will be home soon. Bye-bye.

965
01:20:28,020 --> 01:20:29,479
Bye, Mom.

966
01:20:29,522 --> 01:20:32,642
Patsy Cline... was listening? To me?

967
01:20:33,734 --> 01:20:36,901
- Bye-bye, honey.
- Bye! See you later, Momma!

968
01:20:42,827 --> 01:20:45,365
Hey.

969
01:20:45,413 --> 01:20:48,829
Hey! Did you bring me that beer like I...?

970
01:20:51,168 --> 01:20:55,380
I keep my straw in the top drawer, honey,
right behind you.

971
01:20:55,423 --> 01:20:57,499
Right behind... top drawer.

972
01:21:00,970 --> 01:21:03,046
It's right in there. Thank you.

973
01:21:03,973 --> 01:21:07,638
That's the one. Thank you.

974
01:21:13,649 --> 01:21:15,725
What's the matter with you?

975
01:21:16,736 --> 01:21:20,568
Ain't you ever seen
no glamorous star before?

976
01:21:20,615 --> 01:21:23,651
You ain't mad at me
for singing your song, Patsy?

977
01:21:23,701 --> 01:21:25,279
Mad?

978
01:21:25,328 --> 01:21:27,404
Sit down.

979
01:21:31,083 --> 01:21:35,662
I'm scared because people might think
you sing it better than I do.

980
01:21:35,713 --> 01:21:40,174
- Uh-uh!
- You're stirring things up in this town.

981
01:21:40,217 --> 01:21:43,586
Hey. How many times
you been on the Opry now?

982
01:21:43,638 --> 01:21:45,844
Seventeen straight times.

983
01:21:47,558 --> 01:21:51,722
People wanna know who you been
sleeping with that you been on so much.

984
01:21:51,771 --> 01:21:54,012
Who's been saying that?

985
01:21:54,065 --> 01:21:57,599
Gals that sleep with everybody
and still ain't been on.

986
01:21:57,652 --> 01:22:00,439
- Like who?
- Let me put it this way,

987
01:22:00,488 --> 01:22:03,904
take it as a compliment,
you got 'em running scared.

988
01:22:05,368 --> 01:22:08,534
I can't believe I'm talking to Patsy Cline.

989
01:22:08,579 --> 01:22:13,371
(MC) Patsy Cline has been hospitalised
for several months now.

990
01:22:13,417 --> 01:22:17,166
We are happy to say she is here tonight
to sing for you.

991
01:22:17,213 --> 01:22:20,796
A Grand Ole Opry welcome
for Patsy Cline!

992
01:22:22,051 --> 01:22:24,803
(Man) You're looking hot tonight, girl.

993
01:22:33,104 --> 01:22:43,235
♪ Sweet dreams of you ♪

994
01:22:44,740 --> 01:22:51,573
♪ Every night ♪

995
01:22:51,622 --> 01:22:55,951
♪ I go through ♪

996
01:22:57,003 --> 01:23:03,456
♪ Why can't I forget you ♪

997
01:23:03,509 --> 01:23:09,179
♪ And start my life anew? ♪

998
01:23:09,223 --> 01:23:14,466
♪ Instead of having sweet dreams ♪

999
01:23:15,563 --> 01:23:19,691
♪ About you ♪

1000
01:23:21,444 --> 01:23:27,696
♪ You don't love me ♪

1001
01:23:27,742 --> 01:23:30,908
♪ It's plain... ♪♪

1002
01:23:30,953 --> 01:23:33,361
(Doo) Johnny didn't need any dogs...

1003
01:23:33,414 --> 01:23:36,249
(Woman) Great, Patsy!
(Man) Nice show, Patsy!

1004
01:23:36,292 --> 01:23:41,369
What y'all two devils been up to
besides getting into trouble?

1005
01:23:41,422 --> 01:23:43,000
Delmar, two Co-Colas.

1006
01:23:43,049 --> 01:23:46,252
Mooney says he's gonna
take me squirrel hunting.

1007
01:23:46,302 --> 01:23:48,627
Don't you bring home no squirrels.

1008
01:23:48,679 --> 01:23:52,973
When I left Virginia
I swore I'd never eat another squirrel.

1009
01:23:53,017 --> 01:23:57,311
I love squirrel meat.
Don't you like squirrel, Patsy?

1010
01:23:57,354 --> 01:24:00,640
Of course I do.
I married Charlie, didn't I?

1011
01:24:01,734 --> 01:24:03,810
Charlie, you know I love you.

1012
01:24:05,529 --> 01:24:10,690
Even if I have to remind him he ain't
nothin' but a damn tax deduction.

1013
01:24:10,743 --> 01:24:15,452
That goes for you too, Doolittle Lynn,
and don't you forget it.

1014
01:24:20,086 --> 01:24:24,035
- (Patsy) ♪ Is on us women... ♪
- (Laughter)

1015
01:24:24,090 --> 01:24:30,175
♪ And it's not true
that only you men feel the pain... ♪

1016
01:24:30,221 --> 01:24:32,012
(Man) It's true, it's true!

1017
01:24:32,056 --> 01:24:35,923
♪ Right from the start, most every heart ♪

1018
01:24:35,976 --> 01:24:38,977
♪ That's ever been broken... ♪♪

1019
01:24:40,147 --> 01:24:44,608
- Doo? You all right?
- Yeah.

1020
01:24:45,736 --> 01:24:47,978
Got you enough books?

1021
01:24:49,281 --> 01:24:51,357
(Carnival organ)

1022
01:24:52,910 --> 01:24:55,579
(Fans chattering, indistinct)

1023
01:24:57,206 --> 01:24:59,614
- Have a look.
- She's not in there.

1024
01:24:59,667 --> 01:25:01,576
Get down from there. Let me try.

1025
01:25:01,627 --> 01:25:03,785
(Thunder)

1026
01:25:04,922 --> 01:25:08,671
My Lord, Patsy,
I hope we don't get rained out.

1027
01:25:08,717 --> 01:25:13,011
You don't get rained out on circuits
like these, you just keep singing.

1028
01:25:13,055 --> 01:25:15,593
Mud, flood, hell or high water.

1029
01:25:15,641 --> 01:25:18,097
(Man) Five minutes, Patsy.

1030
01:25:18,144 --> 01:25:21,809
- Looks like that's it for me.
- What else do you wear?

1031
01:25:21,856 --> 01:25:25,189
I start with liquid make-up
and powder that down.

1032
01:25:25,234 --> 01:25:28,685
Get ready cos I'm gonna call you up
after my first song.

1033
01:25:28,737 --> 01:25:30,196
OK.

1034
01:25:32,825 --> 01:25:36,194
(Fan knocking on window)
Somebody moving!

1035
01:25:36,245 --> 01:25:38,321
What did you do that for?

1036
01:25:38,372 --> 01:25:41,373
What have you got on your face?

1037
01:25:41,417 --> 01:25:43,493
I just thought I'd try it.

1038
01:25:44,503 --> 01:25:46,543
- Do you like it?
- No.

1039
01:25:47,631 --> 01:25:50,205
Hell no. You know that I don't like it.

1040
01:25:50,259 --> 01:25:53,176
Get on back there and take it off.

1041
01:25:54,471 --> 01:25:56,797
- No.
- What?

1042
01:25:56,849 --> 01:25:59,007
Hey, now, wait a minute!

1043
01:25:59,059 --> 01:26:02,428
(Man) Loretta Lynn!
(2nd man) I'll be darned!

1044
01:26:05,691 --> 01:26:10,686
♪ I'm back in baby's arms ♪

1045
01:26:10,738 --> 01:26:15,530
♪ How I missed those lovin' arms ♪

1046
01:26:15,576 --> 01:26:19,905
♪ I'm back where I belong ♪

1047
01:26:19,955 --> 01:26:24,035
♪ Back in baby's arms ♪

1048
01:26:25,211 --> 01:26:30,169
- ♪ Don't know why we quarrelled... ♪
- (Man) I'm sorry...

1049
01:26:30,216 --> 01:26:34,712
♪ We never did before ♪

1050
01:26:34,762 --> 01:26:38,510
♪ Since we found how much it hurts ♪

1051
01:26:38,557 --> 01:26:42,769
♪ I bet we never quarrel any more ♪♪

1052
01:26:44,146 --> 01:26:46,933
- No good.
- How do you win a parrot?

1053
01:26:46,982 --> 01:26:48,774
Two out of three.

1054
01:26:50,402 --> 01:26:52,644
One...

1055
01:26:52,696 --> 01:26:56,030
One parrot. Let me know
when I run out of money.

1056
01:26:56,075 --> 01:26:59,241
Get away with every parrot you got.

1057
01:27:02,414 --> 01:27:07,325
- Where you stacking these?
- Put them next to the red trailer.

1058
01:27:07,378 --> 01:27:12,289
Let's move it up. I'm cold, miserable, wet,
I'm gonna lose my voice.

1059
01:27:14,134 --> 01:27:16,542
- Have you seen Doo?
- No, darling.

1060
01:27:16,595 --> 01:27:20,759
(Roadie) Put that in the corner
and put that big thing against it.

1061
01:27:22,559 --> 01:27:26,474
(2nd roadie) Anything else?
(3rd roadie) Yeah, this right here.

1062
01:27:27,606 --> 01:27:32,683
- Put them on top. That's it.
- Everybody, this bus is taking off!

1063
01:27:33,779 --> 01:27:36,650
If you wanna keep that arm,
get it off my husband.

1064
01:27:36,699 --> 01:27:39,865
- Who are you telling what?
- I don't know who you are.

1065
01:27:39,910 --> 01:27:43,244
But I know what you are.
Doo, they're gonna leave.

1066
01:27:43,289 --> 01:27:48,365
If you was keeping your man satisfied
he wouldn't have to go nowhere else.

1067
01:27:48,419 --> 01:27:50,577
- (Bus horn)
- Doo, come on!

1068
01:27:50,629 --> 01:27:54,876
- (Driver) Loretta, let's go!
- Let me get my parrots, baby.

1069
01:27:57,970 --> 01:28:02,133
- (Bus horn)
- (Driver) Loretta!

1070
01:28:02,182 --> 01:28:03,725
Thank you.

1071
01:28:03,767 --> 01:28:05,226
(lnaudible)

1072
01:28:05,269 --> 01:28:08,139
(Horn honking repeatedly,
engine revving)

1073
01:28:08,188 --> 01:28:11,225
Why you in an uproar?
I wasn't doing nothing.

1074
01:28:11,275 --> 01:28:13,232
Yeah, I saw you doing nothing.

1075
01:28:13,277 --> 01:28:16,895
Darlin', I get lonesome,
I need somebody to talk to.

1076
01:28:16,947 --> 01:28:20,897
It didn't look like no talking to me.
I'm warning you, Doo...

1077
01:28:20,951 --> 01:28:24,154
I'd better not catch you
with trash like that again.

1078
01:28:24,204 --> 01:28:26,956
I mean it.

1079
01:28:26,999 --> 01:28:29,075
Warning me?

1080
01:28:29,126 --> 01:28:32,210
Goddamn, don't you ever
warn me about nothing!

1081
01:28:32,254 --> 01:28:34,413
You understand that?

1082
01:28:35,507 --> 01:28:37,583
Hear me talking to you?

1083
01:28:40,804 --> 01:28:42,880
You hear me talking to you?

1084
01:28:50,314 --> 01:28:53,315
♪ Women like you, they're a dime a dozen ♪

1085
01:28:53,359 --> 01:28:56,276
♪ You can buy 'em anywhere ♪

1086
01:28:56,320 --> 01:28:59,736
♪ For you to get to him
I'll have to move over ♪

1087
01:28:59,782 --> 01:29:02,486
♪ And I'm gonna stand right here... ♪

1088
01:29:02,618 --> 01:29:06,865
♪ This is the chorus.
It'll be over my dead body ♪

1089
01:29:06,914 --> 01:29:10,330
♪ So get out while you can ♪

1090
01:29:10,376 --> 01:29:15,666
♪ Cos you ain't woman enough
to take my man ♪♪

1091
01:29:16,757 --> 01:29:19,544
Where the hell
did you get the idea for that?

1092
01:29:19,593 --> 01:29:21,052
Where do you think?

1093
01:29:24,431 --> 01:29:26,756
(Chattering, indistinct)

1094
01:29:27,851 --> 01:29:29,927
Hey, Charlie!

1095
01:29:29,978 --> 01:29:32,600
(Patsy) Charlie!

1096
01:29:33,690 --> 01:29:35,813
Wake up, Charlie.

1097
01:29:37,861 --> 01:29:41,776
- Where the hell you been?
- Shopping. Looks like you have too.

1098
01:29:41,824 --> 01:29:44,990
Get that crap off your face.

1099
01:29:45,035 --> 01:29:49,412
- I like it and it's stayin'.
- Hold on, Mooney, this is my idea.

1100
01:29:49,456 --> 01:29:53,786
- If I wanna wear make-up, I will.
- You'll do whatever I tell you.

1101
01:29:53,836 --> 01:29:55,413
I'll do just what I want!

1102
01:29:55,462 --> 01:29:58,333
- Don't talk to me like that.
- Don't you hit me!

1103
01:29:58,382 --> 01:30:01,051
I'll whip your butt, girl! Goddamn!

1104
01:30:01,093 --> 01:30:04,711
Hey, hey. Come on, let's get in the car.

1105
01:30:04,763 --> 01:30:08,761
Charlie, get in the car and drive.
Loretta, get in!

1106
01:30:08,809 --> 01:30:11,098
Charlie, get in that car and drive.

1107
01:30:11,145 --> 01:30:14,679
(Man) That's Patsy Cline.
(Woman) That's Loretta Lynn!

1108
01:30:14,731 --> 01:30:16,808
- Damn!
- (Man) Hello, Patsy!

1109
01:30:21,822 --> 01:30:25,985
Ain't no chance of gettin' in
that goddamned car, hey, boys?

1110
01:30:27,870 --> 01:30:29,946
(Squealing tyres)

1111
01:30:38,839 --> 01:30:40,713
(Car door slams)

1112
01:30:48,223 --> 01:30:50,893
Oh, my God. Did I do that?

1113
01:30:53,479 --> 01:30:55,555
Is it broke?

1114
01:31:03,530 --> 01:31:05,487
Aren't you gonna talk?

1115
01:31:19,838 --> 01:31:24,880
Baby, I'm gonna get me a job,
driving a truck or being a mechanic,

1116
01:31:24,927 --> 01:31:27,003
doing something that I'm good at.

1117
01:31:28,138 --> 01:31:30,760
You're good at managing me.

1118
01:31:30,807 --> 01:31:33,215
I wouldn't be here if it wasn't for you.

1119
01:31:33,268 --> 01:31:37,017
Getting here's one thing
and being here's another.

1120
01:31:38,982 --> 01:31:41,853
My job's done,
I'll just get me another one.

1121
01:31:43,278 --> 01:31:45,983
Doo, if it's gonna break us up I'll quit.

1122
01:31:46,031 --> 01:31:48,736
Successful people don't quit, baby.

1123
01:31:53,747 --> 01:31:57,246
Got another one of your headaches,
don't you?

1124
01:32:00,045 --> 01:32:02,121
Just like your daddy.

1125
01:32:02,172 --> 01:32:04,959
Coal dust give him the headache.

1126
01:32:05,008 --> 01:32:07,499
I guess I'm what's giving 'em to you.

1127
01:32:16,270 --> 01:32:18,309
Loretta.

1128
01:32:24,236 --> 01:32:26,988
Figured it was about time.

1129
01:32:44,548 --> 01:32:47,039
Doo.

1130
01:32:50,554 --> 01:32:54,338
(Radio) ♪ For you to get to him,
I'll have to move over ♪

1131
01:32:54,391 --> 01:32:56,799
♪ And I'm gonna stand right here ♪

1132
01:32:57,894 --> 01:33:01,145
♪ It'll be over my dead body ♪

1133
01:33:01,189 --> 01:33:04,523
♪ So get out while you can ♪

1134
01:33:04,568 --> 01:33:09,859
♪ Cos you ain't woman enough
to take my man ♪♪

1135
01:33:13,160 --> 01:33:15,615
I'm pregnant again, Patsy.

1136
01:33:15,662 --> 01:33:17,821
Are you sure?

1137
01:33:25,005 --> 01:33:27,578
I don't wanna have it.

1138
01:33:27,633 --> 01:33:30,124
I've been having babies since I was 14.

1139
01:33:31,219 --> 01:33:34,719
- What does Mooney think?
- He doesn't know.

1140
01:33:34,765 --> 01:33:38,299
Hey, c'mon, you oughta be happy.
I'm tickled.

1141
01:33:38,352 --> 01:33:40,677
We're gonna have a baby!

1142
01:33:40,729 --> 01:33:44,940
I'm gonna give you the biggest
baby shower in Nashville.

1143
01:33:44,983 --> 01:33:47,225
I want you to make a list.

1144
01:33:48,445 --> 01:33:50,521
Then we'll go shopping.

1145
01:33:50,572 --> 01:33:53,241
I saved all of my maternity clothes.

1146
01:33:53,283 --> 01:33:55,406
I got Randy's old things too.

1147
01:33:55,452 --> 01:33:57,990
You're gonna need all this, Loretta.

1148
01:33:59,498 --> 01:34:01,574
(Patsy) Ow!

1149
01:34:01,625 --> 01:34:04,294
- You know, I forgot I had this.
- Oh, Patsy.

1150
01:34:04,336 --> 01:34:07,919
- Can you believe it?
- You scared me.

1151
01:34:07,964 --> 01:34:11,665
- Red drives men wild.
- That's just what I need.

1152
01:34:11,718 --> 01:34:15,253
You never know
when it'll come in handy.

1153
01:34:17,224 --> 01:34:21,056
Anything you can't find
we gonna buy when I get back.

1154
01:34:21,103 --> 01:34:24,721
- Where are you going?
- I got a benefit in Kansas City.

1155
01:34:24,773 --> 01:34:28,308
I didn't know I had that. Maybe I'll keep it.

1156
01:34:28,360 --> 01:34:31,147
This'll take you through your fifth month.

1157
01:34:31,196 --> 01:34:34,399
- Are you sure I can have this?
- Take it.

1158
01:34:34,449 --> 01:34:37,201
I got something with your name on it.

1159
01:34:37,244 --> 01:34:39,616
I love that.

1160
01:34:39,663 --> 01:34:41,869
(Children laughing outside)

1161
01:34:41,915 --> 01:34:45,082
Oh, Patsy, I got to go.
Doo's waiting for me.

1162
01:34:45,127 --> 01:34:47,499
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1163
01:34:47,546 --> 01:34:50,167
All right, I'll call you on Monday.

1164
01:34:50,215 --> 01:34:52,089
- OK.
- We'll go shopping.

1165
01:34:52,134 --> 01:34:54,885
Anything we can't buy... we'll make.

1166
01:34:55,929 --> 01:34:59,179
- Anything we can't make, we'll steal.
- (Laughing)

1167
01:34:59,224 --> 01:35:02,344
- You take care of yourself.
- OK.

1168
01:35:02,394 --> 01:35:04,766
- Thank you, Patsy.
- Bye-bye, darling.

1169
01:35:04,813 --> 01:35:08,431
Take care.
I'm calling you first thing Monday.

1170
01:35:08,483 --> 01:35:14,486
(Patsy on radio) ♪ You don't love me ♪

1171
01:35:14,531 --> 01:35:17,485
♪ It's plain ♪

1172
01:35:18,577 --> 01:35:22,159
♪ I should know ♪

1173
01:35:22,205 --> 01:35:23,949
♪ I'll never wear... ♪

1174
01:35:23,999 --> 01:35:27,747
(DJ) <i>This is a memorial tribute
to the late Patsy Cline,</i>

1175
01:35:27,794 --> 01:35:30,914
<i>tragically killed this morning
